summary: This document is a certification of records from United Airlines in response to a subpoena related to the Epstein case. It includes declarations from custodians of records confirming the existence and accuracy of certain ticket documentation, as well as a certification of no records for other requested documents.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Ghislaine Maxwell is mentioned in the context of the subpoena response related to ticket documentation for the investigation.

keyFacts: The document certifies that certain records related to ticket documentation were maintained by United Airlines.
The records were requested in a subpoena related to the Epstein investigation.
The document includes a certification of no records for other requested documents, indicating that they may exist but are not in possession of United Airlines.
The document was executed on January 28, 2020.
Ghislaine Maxwell is referenced as a key figure in the investigation.
